edu.hse.cs.tree

Interface IParent<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ImmutableParentNode, ImmutableRootNode, MutableParentNode, MutableRootNode

    public interface IParent<T>
    Each parent has its' children set, where each child is unique (no duplicates).

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean contains(T childValue)
      Checks that this node contains a child with specified value stored in it.

      Recursive version of contains - method.
      java.util.Collection<? extends IChild<T>> getAllDescendants()
      Retrieves all descendants of the node, i.e. children, children's children and so on.
      java.util.Set<? extends IChild<T>> getChildren()
      Any parent node provides a view on its' children set, so that nobody but parent can control (change) the content of the child set.
